What exactly are Botox Injections



Botox injections are a popular method to temporarily erase fine lines and wrinkles around the face. Unlike more invasive cosmetic surgery treatments like a facelift, botox treatments are quick, easy, relatively painless, and require no recovery time. The effects of botox do not last forever, but as long as you can afford to have botox treatments every few months, you'll be able to keep age away and stay looking youthful for as long as you want.

What's botox and what exactly are botox treatments made from?

Botox is the most popular reputation for an ingredient called botulinum toxin A, a type of neurotoxin made by Clostridium botulinum. Botulism is an extremely severe type of food poisoning whereby toxins produced attack the nervous system and cause paralysis, and in serious cases, this can prove fatal. But although the botulinum toxin A is a potentially fatal neurotoxin, it was initially discovered within the late 1970s that the botulinum toxin had therapeutic applications and the toxin began to be used for the management of several disorders from the nervous system.

Botox is still used for numerous medicinal treatments, but it is perhaps extensively known for its application in anti-aging treatments for both women and men. When employed for cosmetic purposes, botox injections are utilized to reduce deep frown lines between your eyes. The injection is not meant to paralyse the face area as many people think, but merely to relax the muscles and stop the individual from frowning or subconsciously grimacing, thus creating further lines and deep wrinkles.

How are botox injections completed?

The botulinum toxin comes as a crystalline substance as well as in order to inject it in to the body, it should be put into a liquid, typically saline. The area of face to become injected is cleaned and a local anaesthetic is used to reduce the discomfort. Once the anaesthetic has taken effect, botox is injected.

