What goes on after the botox procedure?

You'll have to sit inside a semi upright position for some minutes to ensure that you are feeling okay following the procedure. Additionally, you will be told not to lay down for between 2 and 4 hours to prevent the botox from drifting right into a different area of the face. Strenuous exercise should be avoided for some hours to reduce the chance of bruising. Certain medication, particularly aspirin and ibuprofen, ought to be avoided to reduce the chance of bruising.

Just how long will it require the botox to consider effect?

It will take between 3 and 10 days for you to see the results of the botox injections. Very deep lines over the forehead will not disappear completely, however they will disappear. Faint lines about the eyes and over the forehead ought to be almost invisible once the botox has taken effect. For deeper lines, it might be necessary to have more than one treatment.

How long will the botox last?

The effects of botox normally last very well for 3-4 months, but over time you will notice the muscles returning to their normal function. However, is a result of botox will vary based on the skill of the practitioner and achieving the procedure carried out by a novice physician can lead to less than satisfactory results.

What are the risks of botox treatments?

Although botox injections are considered to be safe, there are a few minor risks associated with the procedure. Many people experience discomfort in the botox treatments including headaches and flu-like symptoms. Another side-effect sometimes seen after botox injections is really a drooping eyelid or eyebrow, but when the botox injections are carried out by an established cosmetic surgeon, this is a very rare occurrence.

What are the people who shouldn't have botox injections?

Botox injections contain albumin, so if you are allergic to egg, you must not have botox treatments. Botox ought to be avoided if you're pregnant.

